<br>
doesnt work well with lower level earth pets as thier root doesnt last all that long. <br>
<br>
agro kiting works better at low lvls <br>
get sow for you and your pet. makes sure the mob your fighting is slower than sow. turn taunt off on the pet. nuke the hell outta the mob. send pet. when mob gets close to you run. when it turns on the pet. turn and nuke some more. this works best with water pets ive found. they heal faster than the other pets. and tend to be the most damaging pets.<br>
<br>
at 20 fire starts to tank somewhat decently. and its innate dmg sheild is better than what you cast. fire pets are always a good option until 52 when they turn into crappy wizzards. <br>
<br>
of course you can always just get aego on your lvl 12 fire pet ( no buff lvl limit for pets) and send him into the middle of a ton of mobs. just make sure to hit each one for at least 1 point of dmg. hard part of this is finding the cleric to buff thats in a zone your gunna be hunting in. and waiting for that pet to heal when the fights over. <br>
<br>
my thoughts on pets. <br>
earth: good if you need a mob to stay parked while you nuke but gets the snot beat out of it every time. i only use this pet when i cant let something run away. <br>
fire: between 20 and 50 my personal pet of choice: altho monster summoning 1 and 2 are nice if you find one that self damage sheilds. fair to low hp but the ds makes up for it. <br>
water: good all around pet. the most damaging pet not including damage sheilds. reasonable hp and regen on pet is nice.<br>
air: good grouping pet. healers love the stuns. effective against casters. has no hp so dont let him tank. <br>
<br>
